00:28:53.043 --> 00:28:54.865
world,
for most things that you're

00:28:54.865 --> 00:29:01.189
going to see in the world.
So we're going to look at what

00:29:01.189 --> 00:29:07.559
are called differentiated
products.

00:29:07.559 --> 00:29:11.136
In particular,
we're going to look at a

00:29:11.136 --> 00:29:16.878
particular version of this that
we're going to call the linear

00:29:16.878 --> 00:29:19.518
city model.
So what do I mean by products

00:29:19.518 --> 00:29:21.828
being differentiated?
So I started off with an

00:29:21.828 --> 00:29:24.586
example that's pretty bad for
this story, namely,

00:29:24.586 --> 00:29:26.643
Coke and Pepsi.
